Whenever it determines that there may be a violation of the provisions of this chapter by a manufacturer or dealer of mobile homes, the department may give notice of hearing, and, within 30 days after giving notice, a hearing shall be held by the office of administrative hearings (
AS 44.64.010
) to determine whether there has been a violation. After notice and hearing,

Sec. 45.30.100.   Definitions.
In this chapter,
(1) buyer means a person who purchases a mobile home for personal use and not for purposes of resale;
(2) department means the Department of Law;
(3) mobile home means a vehicle designed and equipped for human habitation, and which may be drawn by a motor vehicle only when authorized by permit.
